e%20more%20frequent%20SpaceX%20launches%20off%20the%20California%20coastline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20says%20the%20commission%20unfairly%20asserted%20regulatory%20powers%20because%20it%20disagreed%20with%20Musk's%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20California%20Coastal%20Commission%2C%20which%20regulates%20the%20use%20of%20land%20and%20water%20in%20the%20state's%20coastal%20zone%2C%20%26quot%3Bhas%20engaged%20in%20naked%20political%20discrimination%26quot%3B%20against%20SpaceX%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20alleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20says%20the%20commission's%20decision%20is%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20First%20and%2014th%20Amendments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThankfully%2C%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20free%20speech%20and%20due%20process%20enshrined%20in%20our%20Constitution%20prohibit%20precisely%20this%20kind%20of%20political%20witch%20hunting%20and%20abuse%20of%20power%20by%20rogue%20state%20agency%20officials%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20commission%20denied%20a%20request%20by%20the%20US%20Space%20Force%20to%20increase%20the%20number%20of%20annual%20Falcon%209%20rocket%20launches%20from%2036%20to%2050%20at%20the%20Vandenberg%20Space%20Force%20Base.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%206-4%20vote%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20SpaceX%2C%20as%20a%20private%20company%2C%20was%20not%20exempt%20from%20obtaining%20a%20permit%2C%20even%20though%20it%20works%20closely%20with%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Musk's%20politics%20weren't%20referenced%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocuments.coastal.ca.gov%2Freports%2F2024%2F10%2FTh9a%2FTh9a-10-2024-report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20were%20discussed%20during%20a%20public%20meeting%20by%20commission%20members.%20Commissioner%20Gretchen%20Newsom%20said%20Musk%20was%20%26quot%3Bspewing%20and%20tweeting%20political%20falsehoods%26quot%3B%20and%20accused%20him%20of%20prioritizing%20profits%20over%20employee%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommission%20chair%20Caryl%20Hart%20added%20Musk%20had%20%26quot%3Baggressively%20injected%20himself%20into%20the%20presidential%20race.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Commission's%20public%20hearing%20record%20indisputably%20shows%20overt%2C%20and%20shocking%2C%20political%20bias%2C%26quot%3B%20SpaceX's%20lawsuit%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20pretext%20%E2%80%94%20the%20political%20basis%20of%20the%20Commission's%20action%20is%20plain%20for%20all%20to%20see.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3BTo%20make%20it%20even%20clearer%20that%20the%20Commission's%20decision%20was%20based%20on%20its%20political%20biases%20and%20other%20irrelevant%2C%20misplaced%20concerns%2C%20the%20Commission%20recently%20approved%20another%20commercial%20space%20launch%20operator%20launching%20up%20to%2060%20launches%20a%20year%20from%20the%20same%20Base%2C%20accepting%20that%20this%20operator's%20launch%20program%2C%20including%20commercial%20launches%2C%20are%20federal%20agency%20activities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20post%20on%20X%20before%20the%20lawsuit%20was%20filed%2C%20Musk%20called%20the%20commissioners'%20comments%20%26quot%3Bincredibly%20inappropriate%26quot%3B%20and%20vowed%20to%20retaliate%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20done%20more%20to%20advance%20sustainable%20energy%20%26amp%3B%20help%20the%20environment%20than%20maybe%20anyone%20ever%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1846281675430334854%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMusk%20wrote%20on%20Tuesday%20in%20a%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20is%20not%20exactly%20a%20'far-right'%20position.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20commission%20%26quot%3Bshould%20resign%20immediately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20SpaceX%20nor%20the%20California%20Coastal%20Commission%20immediately%20responded%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bdf5bf38-5880-4abf-b7f3-520387116149%5C%22%3EWhat%20Musk%20will%20need%20to%20prove%20in%20order%20to%20win%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELegal%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20a%20day%20before%20the%20lawsuit%20was%20filed%20that%20Musk's%20complaint%20could%20be%20successful%20%E2%80%94%20if%20Musk%20can%20prove%20bias.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20Amendment%20scholar%20Eugene%20Volokh%20said%20victory%20for%20Musk%20will%20depend%20on%20what%20evidence%20Musk%20has%20that%20his%20political%20speech%20played%20a%20role%20in%20the%20commission's%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDenying%20a%20license%20%E2%80%94%20or%20other%20government%20retaliation%20%E2%80%94%20based%20on%20an%20applicant's%20political%20speech%2C%20or%20the%20political%20speech%20of%20the%20applicant's%20owner%20or%20manager%2C%20generally%20violates%20the%20First%20Amendment%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Volokh%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20law%20at%20UCLA%20and%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Hoover%20Institution%20at%20Stanford%20University.%20%26quot%3BIndeed%2C%20that's%20even%20true%20of%20denial%20of%20a%20contract%2C%20where%20government%20money%20is%20being%20used.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Driesen%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20Syracuse%20University%2C%20noted%2C%20%26quot%3Bpoliticians%20have%20a%20First%20Amendment%20right%20to%20criticize%20Musk%2C%20so%20accusing%20him%20of%20spreading%20falsehoods%20is%20protected%20political%20speech.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%26quot%3B%20Driesen%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bif%20Musk%20could%20show%20that%20the%20decision%20to%20deny%20his%20application%20was%20punishment%20for%20his%20falsehoods%2C%20that%20might%20make%20out%20a%20First%20Amendment%20violation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDriesen%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bany%20good%20court%20would%20reject%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20commission%20punished%20him%20for%20his%20speech%2C%20since%20the%20decision%20was%20based%20on%20other%20grounds.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20professor%20said%20that%2C%20ultimately%2C%20a%20judge%20might%20%26quot%3Badmonish%26quot%3B%20the%20California%20Coastal%20Commission%20and%20point%20out%20that%20commissioners%20cannot%20punish%20applicants%20for%20their%20speech%20through%20their%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVolokh%20said%20if%20the%20commission's%20decision%20was%20based%20on%20other%20grounds%20%26quot%3Band%20would%20have%20been%20reached%20on%20those%20grounds%20even%20setting%20aside%26quot%3B%20Musk's%20politics%2C%20then%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20no%20First%20Amendment%20violation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20if%20a%20court%20concludes%20that%20it's%20more%20likely%20than%20not%20that%20the%20result%20would%20have%20been%20different%20but%20for%20Musk's%20speech%2C%20then%20there%20would%20be%20a%20violation%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Volokh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Kreps%2C%20a%20political%20scientist%20and%20director%20of%20the%20Tech%20Policy%20Institute%20at%20Cornell%20University%2C%20said%20that%20comments%20made%20by%20the%20commissioners%2C%20even%20if%20%26quot%3Bpolitically%20motivated%2C%26quot%3B%20do%20not%20directly%20constitute%20a%20legal%20violation%20of%20Musk's%20free%20speech%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20possible%20that%20the%20lawsuit%20could%20be%20dismissed%20as%20lacking%20grounds%20for%20a%20constitutional%20claim%2C%26quot%3B%20Kreps%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKreps%20pointed%20out%20that%20political%20discourse%20being%20integrated%20into%20regulatory%20matters%20has%20become%20%26quot%3Bincreasingly%20common%20in%20highly%20publicized%20cases%20involving%20influential%20figures%20like%20Musk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20can%20raise%20questions%20about%20the%20impartiality%20of%20such%20bodies%2C%20even%20if%20the%20legal%20framework%20is%20followed%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20company%20filed%20the%20suit%20days%20after%20a%20massive%20win%20for%20SpaceX%20when%20it%20conducted%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-starship-fifth-flight-test-how-to-watch-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuccessful%20test%20flight%3C%2Fa%3E%20Sunday%20of%20its%20Starship%20and%20Super%20Heavy%20booster%20%E2%80%94%20a%20massive%20rocket%20that%20Musk%20hopes%20will%2C%20one%20day%2C%20transport%20humans%20to%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20is%20breaking%20and%20will%20be%20updated.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-free-speech-lawsuit-california-coastal-commission-spacex-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729083004000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670d2d8d6ac7b701e7cacf88%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-free-speech-lawsuit-california-coastal-commission-spacex-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22SpaceX%20sued%20the%20California%20Coastal%20Commission%20after%20the%20state%20agency%20rejected%20a%20plan%20that%20would%20have%20allowed%20for%20more%20launches.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nmusumeci%40businessinsider.com%20(Natalie%20Musumeci%2CGeoff%20Weiss)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-free-speech-lawsuit-california-coastal-commission-spacex-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BIf%20Good%20Neighbourliness%20Is%20Missing...%26quot%3B%3A%20S%20Jaishankar's%20Swipe%20At%20China%2C%20Pak%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20the%20challenges%20faced%20in%20the%20region%2C%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20in%20his%20address%20at%20the%20SCO%20Summit%20in%20Islamabad%20today%20made%20a%20veiled%20reference%20about%20China%20and%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20trust%20is%20lacking%20or%20cooperation%20inadequate%2C%20if%20friendship%20has%20fallen%20short%20and%20good%20neighbourliness%20is%20missing%20somewhere%2C%20there%20are%20surely%20reasons%20to%20introspect%20and%20causes%20to%20address%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20only%20when%20we%20reaffirm%20our%20commitment%20most%20sincerely%20to%20the%20Charter%20that%20we%20can%20fully%20realise%20the%20benefits%20of%20cooperation%20and%20integration%20that%20it%20envisages.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar's%20remarks%20came%20amid%20the%20trust%20deficit%20in%20the%20region%2C%20wherein%20border%20agreements%20have%20been%20unilaterally%20violated%20by%20China%20and%20cross-border%20terror%20being%20used%20as%20an%20instrument%20of%20state%20policy%20by%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETies%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20has%20gone%20into%20a%20deep-freeze%20as%20India%20has%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20dialogue%20can%20happen%20only%20in%20an%20atmosphere%20%26quot%3Bfree%20of%20terror%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20ball%20is%20now%20in%20Pakistan's%20court%20for%20them%20to%20end%20the%20scourge%20of%20terrorism.%20As%20for%20China%2C%20ties%20have%20diminished%20to%20the%20very%20minimum%20after%20Beijing's%20multiple%20unilateral%20actions%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years.%20There%20can%20be%20no%20cooperation%20when%20there%20is%20no%20trust%2C%20and%20that%20is%20what%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20highlighted%20in%20his%20subtle%20reference%20to%20the%20two%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20all%20the%20delegates%20at%20the%20key%20regional%20summit%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20also%20said%20that%20%26quot%3BCooperation%20must%20be%20based%20on%20mutual%20respect%20and%20sovereign%20equality.%20It%20should%20recognize%20territorial%20integrity%20and%20sovereignty.%20It%20must%20be%20built%20on%20genuine%20partnerships%2C%20not%20unilateral%20agendas.%20It%20cannot%20progress%20if%20we%20cherry