20the%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNorth%20Korea%20is%20simply%20following%20through%20on%20what%20they%20said%20they%20would%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Lim%20Eul-chul%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Kyungnam%20University%2C%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20to%20reflect%20the%20North's%20determination%20to%20completely%20eliminate%20any%20premise%20of%20'unification%20by%20absorption'%20into%20the%20South.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKim%20even%20said%20recently%20that%20his%20country%20was%20no%20longer%20interested%20in%20%26quot%3Bliberating%20the%20South%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20now%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20might%20be%20the%20weather.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwathes%20of%20North%20Korea%20were%20hit%20by%20devastating%20floods%20this%20summer%20that%20destroyed%20thousands%20of%20homes%20and%20farms%2C%20killing%20and%20displacing%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPyongyang%20could%20have%20orchestrated%20this%20latest%20round%20of%20conflict%20with%20the%20South%20to%20deflect%20from%20growing%20domestic%20discontent%2C%20Seoul%20officials%20have%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20North's%20claims%20that%20Seoul%20flew%20drones%20over%20Pyongyang%20--%20a%20major%20security%20breach%20--%20have%20appeared%20on%20the%20front%20pages%20of%20the%20country's%20tightly%20controlled%20state%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20bid%20to%20rally%20%26quot%3BNorth%20Korean%20citizens%2C%20who%20have%20grown%20weary%20of%20the%20fake%20dictatorship%20of%20the%20Kim%20family%26quot%3B%2C%20South%20Korea's%20military%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeoul's%20national%20security%20adviser%20Shin%20Won-sik%20said%20%26quot%3BNorth%20Korea%20is%20escalating%20tensions%20in%20order%20to%20tighten%20its%20grip%20over%20its%20unstable%20internal%20affairs%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNorth%20Korea%20is%20a%20regime%20that%2C%20paradoxically%2C%20maintains%20its%20stability%20by%20the%20existence%20of%20external%20threats%20to%20its%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%20in%20a%20state%20broadcast%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20about%20the%20drones%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20North%20says%20South%20Korea's%20military%20has%20been%20flying%20drones%20over%20the%20capital%20Pyongyang%20to%20drop%20anti-regime%20propaganda%20--%20a%20%26quot%3Bremarkable%26quot%3B%20development%20which%20%26quot%3Bshowcases%20one%20of%20the%20pathways%20through%20which%20we%20could%20see%20a%20serious%20bout%20of%20escalation%20between%20the%20two%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20US-based%20analyst%20Ankit%20Panda%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20Korea%2C%20which%20lacks%20robust%20air%20defences%2C%20is%20insecure%20about%20the%20incursions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDrones%20over%20their%20national%20capital%20could%20provide%20the%20kind%20of%20reconnaissance%20in%20a%20time%20of%20war%20that%20would%20allow%20the%20South%20Koreans%20to%20strike%20directly%20at%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20himself%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECheong%20Seong-chang%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Korean%20peninsula%20strategy%20at%20Sejong%20Institute%2C%20said%20the%20reports%20suggest%20%26quot%3Bthe%20breach%20was%20detected%20in%20the%20airspace%20above%20the%20headquarters%20of%20the%20Central%20Committee%20of%20the%20Workers'%20Party%20of%20Korea%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20North%20Korean%20leadership%20would%20have%20been%20greatly%20shocked%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20these%20drones%20were%20just%20dropping%20propaganda%20rather%20than%20seeking%20to%20locate%20Kim's%20office%2C%20it%20is%20still%20a%20problem%20as%20the%20country%20regards%20all%20%26quot%3Bforeign%20content%20as%20a%20subversive%20threat%26quot%3B%2C%20said%20Leif-Eric%20Easley%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Ewha%20University%20in%20Seoul.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Seoul's%20military%20has%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20North%20has%20repeatedly%20sent%20drones%20into%20the%20South%20--%20including%20to%20Seoul's%20district%20of%20Yongsan%2C%20where%20the%20presidential%20compound%20is%20located%2C%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20Russia%20involved%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistoric%20allies%20Russia%20and%20North%20Korea%20have%20drawn%20ever%20closer%20since%20Moscow%20invaded%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeoul%20claims%20Kim%20has%20been%20shipping%20arms%20to%20Moscow%20to%20use%20against%20Kyiv%2C%20and%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelensky%20recently%20accused%20the%20North%20of%20sending%20troops%20to%20Russia's%20army.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20North%20blew%20up%20inter-Korean%20roads%20and%20railways%2C%20ally%20China%20urged%20all%20sides%20to%20avoid%20escalation.%20But%20Russia%20blames%20Seoul%20for%20the%20drones%2C%20saying%20it%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bgross%20encroachment%20on%20the%20sovereignty%26quot%3B%20of%20North%20Korea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia%20and%20North%20Korea%20are%20not%20only%20engaging%20in%20sanctions-violating%20military%20trade%20and%20reviving%20Cold%20War-era%20diplomatic%20commitments%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Easley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20also%20reinforcing%20and%20amplifying%20each%20other's%20political%20propaganda%20in%20attempts%20to%20justify%20and%20normalise%20their%20pariah%20state%20behaviour.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20they%20done%20this%20before%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENorth%20and%20South%20Korea%20have%20long%20been%20locked%20in%20cycles%20of%20escalation%2C%20and%20Pyongyang%20has%20repeatedly%20blown%20up%20key%20infrastructure%20in%20the%20past%20to%20make%20foreign%20policy%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202008%2C%20it%20blew%20up%20a%20cooling%20tower%20at%20a%20nuclear%20complex%20after%20the%20United%20States%20agreed%20to%20remove%20Pyongyang%20from%20its%20list%20of%20states%20that%20sponsor%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20after%20it%20signed%20a%20tension-reducing%20military%20deal%20with%20the%20South%2C%20it%20simultaneously%20detonated%2010%20guard%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20diplomatic%20outreach%20broke%20down%2C%20it%20then%20blew%20up%20a%20liaison%20office%20in%202020%2C%20largely%20out%20of%20frustration%20that%20activists%20in%20the%20South%20were%20sending%20balloons%20carrying%20anti-regime%20propaganda%20leaflets%20across%20the%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729073220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-10%2Fljalfpgg_north-korea-_625x300_16_October_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhy-is-kim-jong-uns-north-korea-blowing-up-roads-railways-to-the-south-6802312%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dynamiting%20inter-Korea%20roads%20and%20railways.%20Threatening%20war%20over%20drone%20incursions%20and%20moving%20nuclear-capable%20weapons%20to%20the%20border.%20North%20Korea%20appears%20very%20unhappy%20with%20the%20South%20at%20the%20moment.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwhy-is-kim-jong-uns-north-korea-blowing-up-roads-railways-to-the-south-6802312%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Netflix%20Sets%20Next%20German%20Film%20About%20True%20Story%20of%20Migrant%20Rescue%20Ship%20Luventa%2C%20Starring%20%E2%80%98All%20The%20Light%20We%20Cannot%20See%E2%80%99%20Lead%20Actor%20Louis%20Hoffman%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729073211000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Funnamed-14.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236179640%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rollin